The paper discusses event management in sensor networks, which involves processing and analyzing large amounts of data in real-time. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning, artificial intelligence, and data analysis. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are likely candidates as they involve developing algorithms and techniques for processing and analyzing data. Additionally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are also possible categories as they deal with the management and analysis of large-scale sensor networks.
